font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The worst aspect of all-terrain vehicles is the way they spoil the surface of the path badly making walking and cycling very difficult if not impossible in some parts of the Peak District.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Even where there are barriers to prevent entry to paths by off-</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">roading</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> vehicles these can often be got round – trail bikes and quad bikes can quite easily go through the normal barriers for cyclists; on Sunday 25</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> August 2013 while carrying out our regular </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Sustrans</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> route litter-pick and general check, 2 quads and a trail bike roared through </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Beeley</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Woods between </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Claywheels</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Lane and </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Oughtibridge</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> in Sheffield so we reported this on 101 (incident number 511).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">e)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I would therefore request that you consider: </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">classifying as restricted byways all unsealed unclassified roads (UUCRs) (</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ie</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> green lanes)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">downgrading all existing unsealed Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATs) to restricted byway status</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">OR, or if this is seen as too draconian a measure, downgrading to restricted byway all unsealed UUCRs and BOATs in National Parks, Areas of Natural Beauty (AONBs) and where part of National Trails</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">provide</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> rights of appeal against refusals by highway authorities to make Traffic Regulation Orders excluding motor vehicles from green lanes.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">2 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>